** What You’ll Do / Job Description **   

  * As a key SRE contributor, you are naturally passionate about delivering solutions on real-time problems with mission-critical cloud native services. People might describe you as obsessed about achieving the high quality & reliability for customers demand! 
  

  * You will ensure cloud systems, software & databases are highly available & performing optimally. Working in an environment where 24/7 up-time is critical, you will be proactive in identifying opportunities for automation. 
  

  * Your technical deliverables will reach the entire engineering organization to enable product teams to continuously deliver features on the vanguard of innovation. 
  

  * Build robust, easy-to-use foundational platforms and tools that enable engineering teams to provision services rapidly, consistently, and securely. 
  * Exemplify cloud-native site reliability best practices. 
  * Write code that is performant, maintainable, clear, and concise. 
  * Employ strong problem-solving skills, with the ability to debug problems in cloud native distributed systems. 
  * Influence and educate the engineering organization to adopt new and improved architectural patterns. 
  * Provide robust documentation for use by engineers to promote self-service 
  * Take calculated risks, champion new ideas, and cultivate your craft. 
  
** What You Bring / Your Skills **   

  * 3+ years of applicable experience 
  * Strong Linux (Kernel highly desirable). 
  * Strong Kubernetes platforms like AKS, EKS, or similar. 
  * Good experience managing cloud platforms ideally Azure (but would be open AWS, GCP or Oracle Cloud) or similar. 
  * Good Scripting / Ability to Read Code 
  * Experience utilizing CI/CD platforms to automate provisioning infrastructure, software builds, tests, and releases. 
  * Empathy to support the needs of software engineers. 
** Advantageous skills **   

  * Administering SQL/NoSQL databases. 
  * Hadoop stack (Cassandra, Zookeeper) would be highly regarded 
  * Configuration Management (Puppet, Salt, Ansible, Terraform, Jenkins, Packer etc.) 
  * Knowledge/interest/experience of Python, C#, Scala, Java or Golang would be desirable. 
  * Familiarity with building flexible and testable Infrastructure as Code modules. 
  
